Class AccessVisitServiceImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openmrs.api.impl.BaseOpenmrsService
      • org.openmrs.module.usagestatistics668.impl.AccessVisitServiceImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.openmrs.api.OpenmrsService, AccessVisitService

    public class AccessVisitServiceImpl
extends org.openmrs.api.impl.BaseOpenmrsService
implements AccessVisitService
    Implementation of our AccessPatientService interface. This class is set in the /metadata/moduleApplicationContext.xml file to be matched to the AccessPatientService interface.

    This class extends BaseOpenmrsService so that there are empty methods for onStartup and onShutdown. This allows shields us from changes to the OpenmrsService interface from forcing us to implement the methods.

    NEVER call "new AccessPatientServiceImpl()....". To use this class, you do:
    Context.getService(AccessPatientService.class).saveAccessPatient(accessPatient)...
    Author:
    Jonathan
